Putin has made Assange his tool. He's using Wikileaks to spread """"disinformation"""" exactly like the old KGB did; just with modern technology. They don't change much, but they alter a few words in a few emails that can make a message say something completely different. It is easier to believe that it wasn't altered if it's done sparingly. Trump used something in a rally yesterday that was a quote from an article referred to in a Podesta email. It was easy for the journalist who wrote the article to refute it's validity by pointing to the original statement in his article. It's usually not that easy. The fact that this was done, tells us clearly that other changes were made.
